<subSubSection id="B5EC5AF3A7D3F226B14DCAEDD5662ED1" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="243ED5E259BCC42086874CC74A0F91D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4337BEE2676D300363BDE9381CA7FBE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
Habitus with more evident discontinuity between pronotum and elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="935B67413744019B6161E4445842986D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1B</figureCitation>
), pronotum widest before base and more rounded laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="604CB6BB80D2205B1F80CAF00AF0B40A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1B</figureCitation>
). Total length 2.2 mm; length without head 2.0 mm; maximum width 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6944AC3DD3C56938213075089A849C8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="64A259074855E2A2893D43D0609D5242" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="7932D3709390982104737C12E2EB6EAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Color</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Very dark brown to blackish dorsally and ventrally, basal antennomeres, base of meso- and metatibia contrastingly of lighter color (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A53052B6F8F1D9551F0C5202EFC1B622" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="504CA1907A328E5C9C3ABDD70270E4F5" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Liodessus spp. nov. Detail of head in dorsal view. L. meridensis (A, B); L. venezuelanus (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682025" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">2C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3125971353DD1E1A7C97821961269F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="D380E4AC17A2075AE3468D3F78ABEB51" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="53C819F4EE12322A6140CF72C3C7A4C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Surface sculpture</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head with few larger and smaller setiferous punctures (Figs 
<figureCitation id="35615FDF5DA068BA9A790F6CDB0FE7C9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8003AB6583EADCBB4A286B6EB4674991" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Liodessus spp. nov. Detail of head in dorsal view. L. meridensis (A, B); L. venezuelanus (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682025" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">2C, D</figureCitation>
); with distinct microreticulation except on middle of head between the eyes. Pronotum and elytron shiny; with moderately dense and coarse setiferous punctation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7123588FD2511824E79F353CB896545E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F60BD0B937F0BC9824F5E788BE90E3EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B7AC2E31D501495073896396FEDCAF3D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="ACB8911141C329B3107B383B5FB0E3FC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Structures</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antenna stout. Head with occipital line; with rounded clypeus. Pronotum with distinct lateral beads; with distinct long and deep basal striae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="7BB2A58CEA2B952E8478037825B82258" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Liodessus spp. nov. L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682024" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">1A, B</figureCitation>
). Elytron with short basal stria; without sutural line; without basal epipleural transverse carina. Metathoracic wings not examined in holotype (in paratype: short, about half the length of elytron).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3F8F0281EEF9707D3691858E8B299FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="09F2D08643A6EB2FD1E772CAA63E8362" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="4FF5CFBCF1193B553793ABA0F09FB2E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Median lobe of aedeagus broadened towards apex, then narrowing in lateral view; also broadening towards tip in ventral view, tip broadly rounded; parameres of simple &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="DA7CBB6BFA08ADBA0E9B0EF4823E8D34" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
&quot; type, two segmented (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="080C48C7AC490ABD66115237E132738A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Liodessus spp. nov. Median lobe ventral and lateral views; parameres outer and inner surfaces, L. meridensis (A); L. venezuelanus (B). Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682026" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00B9DCFFB3726DBFD54DD39AB96F4A8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="9A80E4B47A8BE1646A3B3CD0079F3236" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Female.</emphasis>
Pronotum and/or elytra microreticulate, dull (specimens from Laguna de Gallo); shiny in the single females from Laguna 
<normalizedToken id="7F7117302C4F065BF08F528E7693596E" originalValue="Mucabají">Mucabaji</normalizedToken>
and Gavidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F29C3379CD173E7C994115A86003442" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="915DF8B8911CC5F72E9882D72DF238A6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="85F58CF160D25D1B49ED1E6107CA663E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Variation</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Size variation of the paratypes is TL 2.0-2.3 mm; TL-h 1.8-2.0 mm; MW 0.9-1.1 mm. In few paratypes, the elytral basal stria is not very obvious.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB694923B8B0F4DB8D9237E5FBC552D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="158038D19ACF408FA169500B9A3F8E93" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A856A4EBA0CA45B3D540F181ACA3F0AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Named after the country of origin. The name is an adjective in the nominative singular.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AB4AC1590C05B52566738AB363BAEE1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="comparisons">
<paragraph id="C187911AD9596FAB5874994F23392CA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Comparative notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="531B196EACB6B0A870E7151C3DCE773F" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
Distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC299E473EAE9ADC7FD692D8B8A75A4" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E4D8B0B08A2FE2A11A67FE6FFE32F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Liodessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the diagnostic combination of the following features: Species from Venezuela; beetle relatively small (TL 2.0-2.3 mm); very dark brown to blackish; head without occipital line; pronotal and elytral striae present; wings reduced considerably; shape of median lobe (broad in lateral and ventral view, with its particular shape).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E56B290FEAFAAD0E250ADAE562A6BFC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="bold platform">
<paragraph id="57F42B0A832262D17D98EF166AF6FDA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">BOLD platform.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB87A554E1BD5818E8192E99ACB7B362" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
We provided 1 entry to our BOLD 
<taxonomicName id="64445BC4D871E8509B4E777625437DDF" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F4B0AC1AFD5E394F54E9E5654F42AC9A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Liodessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
project. The species is well delineated from all other 
<taxonomicName id="695DE02A57C44F4C10A9C4CF6F7A2F32" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="95A193B3F45E51E36225D74259D97185" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Liodessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with an uncorrected p-distance of around 8% or more.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0E0B86A36510988209EA70AD11C2A5F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BAAFE985D8A19023EDA55B42BD89778E" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D974E7B4A4D315798A839C2CE9998295" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
Known from around 
<normalizedToken id="4E2120F923C82219B20F6CEAF5B99248" originalValue="Mérida">Merida</normalizedToken>
, Venezuela.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F95A23239B087A1C532C1B4617D49D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="7" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="691FB2DFD32805012C885869F5ACB822" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="739F33F96E91900B8DA0B3DB8A4FECE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">
Collected from shallow water at the edge of high-altitude ponds (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5D2205093CF0FB007369BF8AE2B661F0" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Habitat of Liodessus spp. nov. near Gavidia, Venenzuela, where both new species were collected (collecting event VZ 10 - 0123 - 03 A). Overview (A); detail of shallow water at the edge (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.6.79598.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682027" pageId="0" pageNumber="7">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
